program is 10 pages long.

00:16:45.770 --> 00:16:48.580
This is before it became
$140 million program.

00:16:48.580 --> 00:16:53.640
And one line says, of course MIT
will provide the programs

00:16:53.640 --> 00:16:58.730
that are required to run
them the computer.

00:16:58.730 --> 00:17:01.220
And it doesn't use the word
"software." The word software

00:17:01.220 --> 00:17:02.240
hadn't been invented.

00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:04.440
And I'll show a graph
in a little bit.

00:17:04.440 --> 00:17:07.160
By the end of the program, they
were worried they may not

00:17:07.160 --> 00:17:08.750
make the landing on the
Moon because the

00:17:08.750 --> 00:17:10.230
software wouldn't be ready.

00:17:10.230 --> 00:17:14.170
So the transition I would say
between people bragging about

00:17:14.170 --> 00:17:16.430
how big their computers are and
Apollo, was the beginning

00:17:16.430 --> 00:17:19.250
of people bragging about
how small they are.

00:17:19.250 --> 00:17:21.760
And then also the transition
from idea that hardware was

00:17:21.760 --> 00:17:24.020
really unreliable.

00:17:24.020 --> 00:17:26.579
But one of the things this
computer used was really the

00:17:26.579 --> 00:17:29.315
first silicon chips, integrated
circuits.

00:17:32.030 --> 00:17:38.100
They bought 60% of the entire US
production of semiconductor

00:17:38.100 --> 00:17:39.630
chips in 1964.

00:17:39.630 --> 00:17:43.090
It gave a huge boost to this
budding, very uncertain

00:17:43.090 --> 00:17:45.280
technology.

00:17:45.280 --> 00:17:50.610
And that made the hardware
actually really reliable.

00:17:50.610 --> 00:17:52.420
And like I said, they
never really had a

00:17:52.420 --> 00:17:53.730
hardware failure in fight.

00:17:53.730 --> 00:17:56.940
But there were all kinds of
funky software bugs that they

00:17:56.940 --> 00:17:59.520
kind of uncover and the
beginning of that software

00:17:59.520 --> 00:18:01.260
could kill you too.

